Hello! Hello!

3
00:01:03,239 --> 00:01:05,020
What a surprise!

4
00:01:05,332 --> 00:01:06,747
Thank you.

5
00:01:07,294 --> 00:01:09,348
Thank you very much.

6
00:01:09,646 --> 00:01:11,088
Thank you so much.

7
00:01:11,174 --> 00:01:13,134
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

8
00:01:14,131 --> 00:01:16,086
Thank you very much.

9
00:01:16,586 --> 00:01:20,420
Welcome. And coming up
in this week's show:

10
00:01:21,586 --> 00:01:25,357
Abbie is sideways on ice
in a 911 Turbo...

11
00:01:25,586 --> 00:01:29,834
...Richard drives Jim Clark's
beautiful Lotus 25...

12
00:01:30,351 --> 00:01:32,857
...and I nearly fall over.

13
00:01:35,534 --> 00:01:37,329
That...

14
00:01:37,415 --> 00:01:39,215
- Exciting looking show.
- Right.

15
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:42,912
That is all to come. Now...

16
00:01:42,998 --> 00:01:46,045
Hang on a minute. Does that mean
Howard and Adrian aren't coming on?

17
00:01:46,131 --> 00:01:48,975
No. Haven't got time.

18
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:51,724
We actually begin
with the French.

19
00:01:51,810 --> 00:01:53,781
Er... now, they don't make
a sports car very often,

20
00:01:53,866 --> 00:01:57,350
but when they do,
literally nobody buys it.

21
00:01:57,789 --> 00:02:01,045
We've had
the Venturi Atlantique,

22
00:02:01,171 --> 00:02:04,467
and then there was
the Matra Murena,

23
00:02:04,553 --> 00:02:06,975
and then there was
the Simca Sport.

24
00:02:07,170 --> 00:02:11,600
And all of them fell down the
back of the sofa of history.

25
00:02:11,732 --> 00:02:14,568
Yeah, yeah, but you're
conveniently forgetting to mention

26
00:02:14,654 --> 00:02:16,661
the best of the French
sports car makers.

27
00:02:16,746 --> 00:02:19,224
That's like saying the best
of the airborne plagues.

28
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:21,341
- No.
- The best of the...

29
00:02:21,426 --> 00:02:23,266
No, it isn't.
There is one French maker

30
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:25,421
that's been consistently good
at making sports cars,

31
00:02:25,506 --> 00:02:29,086
and they've made a new one,
and I've been testing it.

32
00:02:39,626 --> 00:02:42,242
It's called the A110,

33
00:02:42,468 --> 00:02:44,617
and it's made by Alpine,

34
00:02:44,703 --> 00:02:46,283
a French sports car firm

35
00:02:46,369 --> 00:02:49,195
who have a history
of hitting the spot.

36
00:02:50,986 --> 00:02:53,341
The original A110,
for example,

37
00:02:53,426 --> 00:02:58,021
won the World Rally
Championship in 1973.

38
00:02:58,106 --> 00:02:59,821
And it's that car
that gives the new one

39
00:02:59,906 --> 00:03:04,563
not only its name
but also its looks.

40
00:03:14,531 --> 00:03:16,181
So, what we have here

41
00:03:16,266 --> 00:03:19,758
is a small, pure,
no-nonsense sports car

42
00:03:19,883 --> 00:03:25,061
aimed squarely at the Porsche
Cayman and the Audi TT.

43
00:03:25,146 --> 00:03:29,399
And this, unfortunately, is
where the problems begin.

44
00:03:30,786 --> 00:03:36,555
You see, this launch version
of the Alpine costs £51,000.

45
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,061
£51,000.

46
00:03:38,146 --> 00:03:42,497
Now, for £1,000 more,
you can have the TT RS.

47
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:45,438
That's the one Clarkson was
driving in the last series.

48
00:03:46,466 --> 00:03:49,742
And that's more powerful,
and it's faster.

49
00:03:50,650 --> 00:03:53,219
And the Porsche Cayman
you buy for £51,000

50
00:03:53,305 --> 00:03:56,861
is also more powerful than
this, and it's a Porsche.

51
00:03:56,946 --> 00:03:59,391
Whereas this is an Alpine.

52
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:02,734
That's something you're going to have
to explain when you're down the pub.

53
00:04:05,941 --> 00:04:08,758
Even the engine
sounds a bit lame.

54
00:04:09,786 --> 00:04:11,741
I don't mean
the noise it makes,

55
00:04:11,826 --> 00:04:14,701
I mean when somebody asks you,
"What's that got, then, mister?"

56
00:04:14,786 --> 00:04:20,524
Because the answer is, "A
four-cylinder 1.8-litre turbo, sonny!"

57
00:04:20,706 --> 00:04:24,250
For over £50,000.
I mean, is that it?

58
00:04:28,266 --> 00:04:31,981
Also, I'm not sure
about the looks.

59
00:04:32,066 --> 00:04:37,181
The original 1960s version
was a masterpiece.

60
00:04:37,266 --> 00:04:41,344
But for me, this modern
reboot doesn't quite work.

61
00:04:46,106 --> 00:04:48,541
The problem, I think,
is that on modern cars

62
00:04:48,626 --> 00:04:52,398
there are rules about things like how
high the headlights are above the ground,

63
00:04:52,484 --> 00:04:55,261
how forgiving the bonnet is
if you run into a pedestrian.

64
00:04:55,422 --> 00:05:00,336
And once you stretch modern
legislation over 1960s design language,

65
00:05:00,506 --> 00:05:04,008
you end up with a sort of
slightly lame tribute act.

66
00:05:05,426 --> 00:05:08,078
So, is there anything good
to report?

67
00:05:09,146 --> 00:05:11,578
Well, thankfully, yes.

68
00:05:13,266 --> 00:05:16,633
For starters, although
Alpine is owned by Renault,

69
00:05:16,826 --> 00:05:22,703
this car is not just a hot Mégane
dressed up in some fancy suit.

70
00:05:23,039 --> 00:05:26,969
The A110 is in fact a
mid-engined, rear-drive sports car

71
00:05:27,055 --> 00:05:30,930
designed from scratch,
on a clean sheet of paper.

72
00:05:35,386 --> 00:05:38,301
The body and the chassis are
made entirely of aluminium.

73
00:05:38,386 --> 00:05:41,221
And the reason for that
is simple - its lightness.

74
00:05:41,306 --> 00:05:43,541
And from that starting point,
the Alpine engineers

75
00:05:43,626 --> 00:05:45,797
nerded their way
through the rest of the car

76
00:05:45,883 --> 00:05:49,578
and shaved off every
spare gram they could find.

77
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:54,227
The seats, for example,
are half the weight

78
00:05:54,313 --> 00:05:57,344
of the ones you'll find
in any hot Renault.

79
00:05:57,524 --> 00:06:00,047
The handbrake is built
into the main callipers,

80
00:06:00,203 --> 00:06:05,861
rather than being separate,
saving another 2.5 kilos.

81
00:06:05,946 --> 00:06:10,644
Even the stereo is a bespoke,
lightweight design.

82
00:06:12,066 --> 00:06:14,001
And then there's
this boot at the front,

83
00:06:14,086 --> 00:06:17,669
which is just deep enough for
a small suitcase like this one.

84
00:06:17,755 --> 00:06:21,481
But now I think about it, putting the
suitcase in there would just add weight.

85
00:06:21,566 --> 00:06:25,461
So what I would do is just pack my
overnight stuff straight in there.

86
00:06:25,546 --> 00:06:27,481
The only downside is
that in the morning,

87
00:06:27,566 --> 00:06:30,611
I have to go outside if
I want a fresh pair of pants.

88
00:06:34,306 --> 00:06:37,361
So, thanks to Alpine's
fanatical diet regime,

89
00:06:37,446 --> 00:06:43,331
this car is 300 kilos lighter
than a Cayman or an Audi TT.

90
00:06:44,666 --> 00:06:47,531
And that has
a profound effect.

91
00:06:50,706 --> 00:06:52,561
Suddenly,
it doesn't really matter

92
00:06:52,646 --> 00:06:56,755
that you've only got 1.8
litres and 248 horsepower.

93
00:06:56,864 --> 00:07:00,211
This thing absolutely
zips along.

94
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:05,302
Nought to 60,
four and a half seconds.

95
00:07:06,986 --> 00:07:10,958
Top speed limited
to 155 miles an hour.

96
00:07:15,346 --> 00:07:17,716
And then,
when you get to a corner...

97
00:07:20,546 --> 00:07:24,271
...you find out just
how agile this thing is.

98
00:07:33,706 --> 00:07:36,251
It's like driving a feather.

99
00:07:44,826 --> 00:07:49,263
It is like a cartoon car. It should
come with those little bubbles saying...

100
00:07:56,552 --> 00:07:59,880
But even though the A110 is
built to minimalist principles,

101
00:07:59,966 --> 00:08:02,121
you never feel like
you're in some miserable,

102
00:08:02,206 --> 00:08:04,571
Spartan track-day car.

103
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:07,921
It has air-con, sat-nav,

104
00:08:08,006 --> 00:08:10,541
phone connectivity -

105
00:08:10,626 --> 00:08:13,357
all the modern things
you want.

106
00:08:15,386 --> 00:08:17,841
This whole lightness
and smallness thing

107
00:08:17,926 --> 00:08:23,381
cascades down in a sort
of waterfall of pure joy.

108
00:08:23,466 --> 00:08:26,001
Lower weight means you
don't need such big tyres,

109
00:08:26,086 --> 00:08:27,601
you don't need so much grip.

110
00:08:27,686 --> 00:08:30,341
That gives the car more feel.

111
00:08:30,426 --> 00:08:35,561
Low weight means you use less
fuel, you make lower emissions.

112
00:08:35,646 --> 00:08:39,013
It's just win-win-win-win
all the way.

113
00:08:39,546 --> 00:08:44,325
This is actually the most intelligent
car I've driven for years.

114
00:08:45,386 --> 00:08:48,333
And I love it for that.
I love it.

115
00:09:02,746 --> 00:09:04,521
Thank you.

116
00:09:04,641 --> 00:09:06,001
Erm...

117
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:11,824
So... So despite
the ordinary engine,

118
00:09:11,958 --> 00:09:13,801
the looks that
you're not sure about,

119
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:16,521
and the high price,
you liked it?

120
00:09:16,607 --> 00:09:18,101
I did. I loved it, yeah.

121
00:09:18,186 --> 00:09:20,919
- Yes, but would you buy one?
- I have.

122
00:09:22,906 --> 00:09:24,721
- You've bought one of those?
- I have.

123
00:09:24,806 --> 00:09:26,581
And actually,
so has Gordon Murray.

124
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:28,281
I've brought
a picture of him along. Him.

125
00:09:28,366 --> 00:09:31,141
He designed the McLaren F1,
so he knows.

126
00:09:31,226 --> 00:09:35,461
Yeah, so it's the sports car of choice
for old men with terrible shirts.

127
00:09:35,546 --> 00:09:37,989
- So that's good to know.
- Evidently.

128
00:09:38,075 --> 00:09:42,531
But, now let's see how fast it goes
round the Eboladrome, shall we?

129
00:09:43,626 --> 00:09:44,927
And she's off.

130
00:09:45,013 --> 00:09:48,721
Brisk start, and a parp from
the exhaust on the up-change.

131
00:09:48,935 --> 00:09:50,921
Immediately onto
the Isn't Straight.

132
00:09:51,006 --> 00:09:54,974
And actually,
that's not hanging around.

133
00:09:55,426 --> 00:09:58,161
Perhaps James was right
about the benefits of...

134
00:09:58,246 --> 00:10:00,901
whatever it was
he was saying.

135
00:10:01,048 --> 00:10:04,503
Howling round
the final bend of the Isn't.

136
00:10:04,669 --> 00:10:09,302
Dropping down now
into Your Name Here.

137
00:10:09,388 --> 00:10:11,481
Scrubbing off speed
in a hurry.

138
00:10:11,566 --> 00:10:15,513
Torturing those tyres, but
that does look pretty nimble.

139
00:10:15,886 --> 00:10:20,357
Now, the canter back down
the Isn't, picking up speed.

140
00:10:21,325 --> 00:10:24,333
Dab of brakes
at the mid-point.

141
00:10:25,763 --> 00:10:27,638
Now much harder
on the brakes,

142
00:10:27,724 --> 00:10:30,721
flicking down the seven-speed
box for Old Lady's House.

143
00:10:30,911 --> 00:10:32,661
Any understeer?

144
00:10:32,794 --> 00:10:34,982
No, not bad
for a mid-engined car

145
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:36,721
with no weight over the nose.

146
00:10:36,806 --> 00:10:39,681
I actually rather
like the styling of this,

147
00:10:39,766 --> 00:10:41,341
and I'm right.

148
00:10:41,426 --> 00:10:44,396
Just Field of Sheep
to go now.

149
00:10:44,546 --> 00:10:46,061
Here we are.

150
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:48,888
And oh, yes, that's an
exuberant drift to finish,

151
00:10:49,001 --> 00:10:50,726
and across the line!

152
00:10:51,506 --> 00:10:53,261
Very good.

153
00:10:53,346 --> 00:10:55,321
Very good.
Good driving, on form.

154
00:10:57,086 --> 00:10:58,802
Right.

155
00:10:59,546 --> 00:11:02,681
Right, let's see where it
goes on our lap board.

156
00:11:02,766 --> 00:11:05,333
Will it go in the top ten?

157
00:11:05,565 --> 00:11:07,520
Oh, dear, no, it doesn't.

158
00:11:07,786 --> 00:11:09,536
Sorry, May, that is dismal

159
00:11:09,622 --> 00:11:11,861
for a mid-engined car.
It is.

160
00:11:11,946 --> 00:11:14,921
It isn't about things like
lap times. I told you before.

161
00:11:15,006 --> 00:11:17,121
He who is first
shall be last,

162
00:11:17,206 --> 00:11:19,261
and the last
shall be first.

163
00:11:19,346 --> 00:11:21,121
- Yes, but it's 15th.
- It is, yeah.

164
00:11:21,206 --> 00:11:23,771
- It is, it is.
- So?

165
00:11:23,919 --> 00:11:27,114
It's the Romain Grosjean
of cars, that is.

166
00:11:27,239 --> 00:11:28,888
- Romain who?
- Grosjean.

167
00:11:28,974 --> 00:11:30,721
- Who's he?
- He's a French racing driver.

168
00:11:30,806 --> 00:11:34,036
The 15th best Formula One
driver in the world, in fact.

169
00:11:34,153 --> 00:11:36,171
- You'd like him.
- I already do.

170
00:11:36,257 --> 00:11:37,880
Good. Good,
so we've sorted that out.

171
00:11:37,959 --> 00:11:40,825
It's time for us to move on,
because right now it is time

172
00:11:40,911 --> 00:11:44,896
for us to scrump
an apple of chat

173
00:11:45,029 --> 00:11:47,564
from the orchard
of intercourse,

174
00:11:47,649 --> 00:11:50,684
which is on
Conversation Street.

175
00:11:56,869 --> 00:11:58,844
- I like that one.
- I thought you would.

176
00:11:58,929 --> 00:12:01,927
- I like that one a lot.
- That's so up your street.

177
00:12:02,247 --> 00:12:05,732
Um... right now, lots of
people these days

178
00:12:05,818 --> 00:12:07,104
are buying old cars,

179
00:12:07,189 --> 00:12:09,216
and we think we can see why.

180
00:12:09,341 --> 00:12:12,216
Yeah, because an old Jaguar
E-Type, or Alfa Spider,

181
00:12:12,302 --> 00:12:15,013
is far more interesting to
look at than any modern car,

182
00:12:15,099 --> 00:12:16,521
and it won't depreciate.

183
00:12:16,607 --> 00:12:18,310
In fact,
it'll make you money.

184
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:21,622
Yeah, the trouble is, though,
you get into your old car,

185
00:12:21,739 --> 00:12:23,534
and it's crap.

186
00:12:24,269 --> 00:12:25,544
He's absolutely right,

187
00:12:25,629 --> 00:12:27,974
we forget how terrible
old cars were, really.

188
00:12:28,060 --> 00:12:29,964
I mean, if you go more
than 40 miles an hour,

189
00:12:30,049 --> 00:12:33,099
the windscreen wipers part
company with the windscreen.

190
00:12:33,185 --> 00:12:36,224
- Yes.
- And the headlamps are like candles in jam jars.

191
00:12:36,309 --> 00:12:38,644
- And the demister doesn't.
- No, it doesn't.

192
00:12:38,729 --> 00:12:40,304
- And the heater doesn't.
- No.

193
00:12:40,389 --> 00:12:42,204
And everything else rattles,
and the brakes don't work.

194
00:12:42,289 --> 00:12:44,344
- Exactly.
- That's old cars, they were...

195
00:12:44,429 --> 00:12:47,524
I speak from experience. I've
got a 40-year-old Ferrari, a 308.

196
00:12:47,609 --> 00:12:52,184
Apart from all those things, it's
catastrophically slow. You wouldn't believe it.

197
00:12:52,269 --> 00:12:54,624
I pull away from lights, and people
behind honk because they think,

198
00:12:54,709 --> 00:12:56,244
- "That's a Ferrari, that'll... Oh."
- Yeah.

199
00:12:56,329 --> 00:12:58,804
They honk? Doesn't that
happen in any car you drive?

200
00:12:58,889 --> 00:13:01,124
- No, no, no...
- "Oh, get out of the way!"

201
00:13:01,209 --> 00:13:02,384
Pretty much.

202
00:13:02,469 --> 00:13:03,684
But it is unbelievable
just how poor it is.

203
00:13:03,769 --> 00:13:05,104
Very slow.

204
00:13:05,189 --> 00:13:07,604
But that's the exact point
we're trying to make here.

205
00:13:07,689 --> 00:13:10,524
There are now loads of companies
who will take an old car

206
00:13:10,609 --> 00:13:12,544
and then gently modernise it.

207
00:13:12,629 --> 00:13:15,164
Got some examples here
of what we're on about.

208
00:13:15,249 --> 00:13:18,064
There's this, which
is the Singer Porsche,

209
00:13:18,149 --> 00:13:19,524
I'm obviously not
very interested in that.

210
00:13:19,609 --> 00:13:21,604
These two are,
but I couldn't care less.

211
00:13:21,689 --> 00:13:24,704
Then you've got the Eagle,
er... E-Type Speedster,

212
00:13:24,789 --> 00:13:27,104
one of the best-looking cars
I've ever seen.

213
00:13:27,189 --> 00:13:31,104
That's an actual E-Type, and one of the
most beautiful to drive. Absolute honey.

214
00:13:31,189 --> 00:13:34,644
Yeah, there's a company in Germany
now, and they are modernising lightly.

215
00:13:34,729 --> 00:13:36,664
Remember those old
Mercedes Pagoda SLs?

216
00:13:36,749 --> 00:13:38,724
- Oh, yeah.
- They're putting AMG engines in.

217
00:13:38,809 --> 00:13:41,719
What, mo... That's got a
modern AMG engine in it?

218
00:13:41,829 --> 00:13:44,337
Do you want to have a
look at the engine? Another shot.

219
00:13:44,422 --> 00:13:46,202
- Hang on. 
- There it is, look at that!

220
00:13:46,288 --> 00:13:48,744
- That is a car.
- I see you like that.

221
00:13:48,829 --> 00:13:50,986
- Very, very much.
- I've got something you'll like more.

222
00:13:51,071 --> 00:13:52,944
- Have you?
- Mm-hm.

223
00:13:53,029 --> 00:13:54,944
Oh, my God!

224
00:13:55,029 --> 00:13:57,044
That is an old
'68 Dodge Charger.

225
00:13:57,129 --> 00:13:58,891
- You used to have one.
- I did.

226
00:13:58,977 --> 00:14:04,633
But someone has put in that a
1,000-horsepower modern-day Hellcat engine.

227
00:14:04,719 --> 00:14:05,784
Aw!

228
00:14:05,869 --> 00:14:07,469
- I mean...
- I...

229
00:14:07,563 --> 00:14:09,814
I need some time alone...

230
00:14:10,989 --> 00:14:13,184
- with that picture.
- It's just...

231
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:15,469
That is such
a good idea, this, I think.

232
00:14:15,555 --> 00:14:17,404
It is actually, and
it's a very good point.

233
00:14:17,489 --> 00:14:20,864
We all think we would like a
Jensen Interceptor, don't we?

234
00:14:20,949 --> 00:14:22,424
But the fact is it won't go,

