00:14:22,509 --> 00:14:25,064
it won't stop if it ever does
go, the brakes won't work,

236
00:14:25,149 --> 00:14:26,684
all the rest of it -
terrible thing.

237
00:14:26,769 --> 00:14:29,144
But here is
a Jensen Interceptor,

238
00:14:29,229 --> 00:14:31,764
but that has modern brakes,
has a modern cooling system,

239
00:14:31,849 --> 00:14:34,321
and it has the engine
from a Corvette.

240
00:14:34,453 --> 00:14:37,305
No, it does. I've actually driven
that very car, and it's epic.

241
00:14:37,391 --> 00:14:39,069
Well, that one isn't
anymore, because somebody

242
00:14:39,154 --> 00:14:40,670
wrapped it round a
fence in Goodwood.

243
00:14:40,756 --> 00:14:42,607
- Spoiled it.
- But it was epic before that.

244
00:14:42,693 --> 00:14:44,561
It's a fantastic car, it really, really is.

245
00:14:44,646 --> 00:14:46,564
I'd like to explain, by the
way, that squeaking noise

246
00:14:46,649 --> 00:14:48,624
is not James thinking,
it's...

247
00:14:49,809 --> 00:14:51,064
...it's the wind.

248
00:14:51,149 --> 00:14:53,404
- It's quite a breezy day.
- It's a breezy day.

249
00:14:53,489 --> 00:14:57,184
And we decided to base ourselves
in a tent because we're mad.

250
00:14:57,269 --> 00:14:58,778
- And on a hill.
- And on a hill.

251
00:14:58,864 --> 00:15:00,099
But I think the problem

252
00:15:00,185 --> 00:15:01,997
with all of these
reimagined cars

253
00:15:02,083 --> 00:15:04,528
is that they're expensive,
they're too expensive.

254
00:15:04,622 --> 00:15:07,567
That Mercedes Pagoda SL,
that's £300,000,

255
00:15:07,669 --> 00:15:09,824
those Singer Porsches,
£400,000,

256
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:13,464
that E-Type Speedster,
650 grand - it's just crazy.

257
00:15:13,549 --> 00:15:16,372
The problem is that the companies
who are doing this kind of work,

258
00:15:16,551 --> 00:15:18,703
they know they can charge
that kind of money,

259
00:15:18,789 --> 00:15:20,989
cos the customers
that come to their workshops

260
00:15:21,075 --> 00:15:23,755
invariably arrive
in a helicopter

261
00:15:23,942 --> 00:15:28,239
with a Ukrainian girlfriend
and Lewis Hamilton's watch.

262
00:15:28,325 --> 00:15:30,356
And the fact is, if you're
gonna dress up like that

263
00:15:30,442 --> 00:15:31,964
and act like that,
if you're gonna show off,

264
00:15:32,049 --> 00:15:33,684
you'll get ripped off,
that's the way it is.

265
00:15:33,769 --> 00:15:36,464
- They charge accordingly, don't they?
- That's asking for it.

266
00:15:36,549 --> 00:15:38,372
What you should do is
ring them up and say,

267
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:40,031
"Could you collect me from the station?"

268
00:15:40,116 --> 00:15:41,263
- No.
- That'd be better.

269
00:15:41,349 --> 00:15:43,357
No, the bus stop. "Pick
me up from the bus stop",

270
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:44,842
I've come to look at
these cars you're making."

271
00:15:44,927 --> 00:15:47,388
I've just had a thought.
Right, picture this.

272
00:15:47,474 --> 00:15:49,810
An original Opel Manta A.
Remember the one?

273
00:15:49,896 --> 00:15:51,724
- The round taillights?
- Yeah... yeah, black bonnet.

274
00:15:51,809 --> 00:15:55,294
But with the engine from a
modern Vauxhall VXR in it.

275
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:57,497
So I just find some blokes
that'll do that for me,

276
00:15:57,583 --> 00:16:02,817
I do that on the phone, and then I go
and visit them on the bus in a tracksuit.

277
00:16:03,122 --> 00:16:04,704
And you'll get charged
50 quid.

278
00:16:04,789 --> 00:16:07,484
Well, probably 40, cos I need a
tenner to get home on the bus.

279
00:16:08,966 --> 00:16:10,384
Ooh, now.

280
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:12,144
There's a new electric car

281
00:16:12,229 --> 00:16:14,466
from, you're not
going to believe this...

282
00:16:14,575 --> 00:16:16,664
- Kalashnikov.
- Really?

283
00:16:16,749 --> 00:16:20,435
Yeah, the people who make AK-47s are
going to start making electric cars.

284
00:16:20,521 --> 00:16:21,817
I like the sound of that.

285
00:16:21,903 --> 00:16:24,444
Do you want to see
a picture of it? Here it is.

286
00:16:24,529 --> 00:16:26,424
- Ah.
- Oh.

287
00:16:26,509 --> 00:16:30,247
No, don't laugh, because from
the back it's actually worse.

288
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:32,604
- There you go.
- You're right, it is.

289
00:16:32,689 --> 00:16:36,325
Now, I assumed that it would
have eight moving parts,

290
00:16:36,411 --> 00:16:39,104
that you could bury it
in a bog for three months

291
00:16:39,302 --> 00:16:41,326
and that it would only jam
if Richard Hammond used it.

292
00:16:41,411 --> 00:16:42,784
Yes, all right.

293
00:16:42,869 --> 00:16:46,304
But they say it has
revolutionary technology.

294
00:16:46,389 --> 00:16:49,504
Does it? Does it have
central locking, and loading?

295
00:16:49,955 --> 00:16:52,290
More importantly, can you fire
it in the air at weddings?

296
00:16:52,422 --> 00:16:53,504
You probably would.

297
00:16:53,589 --> 00:16:55,703
"Exam results, children,"
they go out and do that.

298
00:16:55,805 --> 00:16:58,704
No, but I think the idea of driving
a car called a Kalashnikov...

299
00:16:58,789 --> 00:17:01,328
- It sounds brilliant.
- Oh, yeah, pretty good.

300
00:17:01,446 --> 00:17:03,852
Yeah. "What are you
driving these days, Rich?"

301
00:17:03,938 --> 00:17:06,304
- "Well, it's a Kalashnikov."
- There you go.

302
00:17:06,389 --> 00:17:07,634
- There you go.
- The problem is,

303
00:17:07,719 --> 00:17:09,843
I reckon they're gonna
sell a lot of T-shirts

304
00:17:09,929 --> 00:17:12,044
and mugs and hats
with the name on,

305
00:17:12,129 --> 00:17:13,904
but not many actual cars.

306
00:17:13,989 --> 00:17:16,544
- Like Ferrari?
- Basically Ferrari, yeah.

307
00:17:16,894 --> 00:17:18,875
Oh, er, here's one.

308
00:17:18,961 --> 00:17:20,804
There's a story I got
from the Dorset Echo,

309
00:17:20,889 --> 00:17:23,384
which is a local newspaper
in Dorset.

310
00:17:23,469 --> 00:17:27,344
And, um... I think it wins the
award for unnecessary reporting,

311
00:17:27,429 --> 00:17:29,404
because it's about
a crash that happened

312
00:17:29,489 --> 00:17:31,624
between
a motorcyclist and a tank.

313
00:17:31,709 --> 00:17:35,604
Happened... Yeah, happened near that
army base down there. OK, and it says,

314
00:17:35,689 --> 00:17:39,464
"The motorcyclist sustained a
suspected fracture to his arm and leg."

315
00:17:39,549 --> 00:17:41,404
And here's the line
they probably didn't need:

316
00:17:41,489 --> 00:17:43,324
"The driver of the tank
was uninjured."

317
00:17:43,409 --> 00:17:44,984
- Oh, was he?
- No?

318
00:17:45,069 --> 00:17:47,804
Well, he was lucky to get
away with that, wasn't he?

319
00:17:47,889 --> 00:17:50,544
Was he really?

320
00:17:50,629 --> 00:17:52,884
I suspect he got back to base
and went, "I hit a what?"

321
00:17:52,969 --> 00:17:55,144
"Did I?"

322
00:17:55,229 --> 00:17:57,633
Good conversation here, I think.
Very good conversation.

323
00:17:57,719 --> 00:17:59,567
Because they've
announced a new type

324
00:17:59,653 --> 00:18:01,564
of motor racing
championship for women.

325
00:18:01,649 --> 00:18:03,584
It's called the W Series, OK?

326
00:18:03,669 --> 00:18:06,633
And the idea is is that
potentially quite good, you know,

327
00:18:06,719 --> 00:18:10,711
women racing drivers can
take part in this series.

328
00:18:10,797 --> 00:18:12,504
Cars are all
exactly the same,

329
00:18:12,589 --> 00:18:13,884
you're invited
to take part,

330
00:18:13,969 --> 00:18:16,904
and the prize money
is £1.1 million.

331
00:18:16,989 --> 00:18:19,492
So, it's, you know,
fairly incentivised.

332
00:18:19,578 --> 00:18:21,189
There's actually been
a lot of discussion about it,

333
00:18:21,274 --> 00:18:22,946
or actually debate,
I should say.

334
00:18:23,032 --> 00:18:26,864
Cos some people are saying it's sexist
to have a women-only championship.

335
00:18:26,949 --> 00:18:29,781
But if you think about it, you've
got women-only football, and rugby

336
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:31,742
and hockey - all Olympic
sports, pretty much,

337
00:18:31,828 --> 00:18:33,391
are segregated
between men and women,

338
00:18:33,477 --> 00:18:35,048
so I can't see why motor
racing should be different.

339
00:18:35,133 --> 00:18:36,992
Not all sports, though.
Men and women compete

340
00:18:37,078 --> 00:18:39,284
directly against each other
in dressage.

341
00:18:39,369 --> 00:18:41,624
Yeah, but that's not a sport.
It isn't.

342
00:18:41,709 --> 00:18:44,924
That's just sitting on a horse
while it tries to look camp.

343
00:18:47,069 --> 00:18:48,644
All right, then, they can...

344
00:18:48,729 --> 00:18:50,504
He's right.

345
00:18:50,589 --> 00:18:52,164
It is, though.

346
00:18:52,249 --> 00:18:53,624
You're right, actually.

347
00:18:53,709 --> 00:18:55,764
There's no segregation, then,
between men and women

348
00:18:55,849 --> 00:18:57,604
in sailing, they compete
against each other.

349
00:18:57,689 --> 00:19:01,224
That's not a sport either,
is it? Sailing is a job.

350
00:19:01,309 --> 00:19:02,984
You have to pull
pieces of rope...

351
00:19:03,069 --> 00:19:04,764
- All right, then!
- It's manual labour.

352
00:19:04,849 --> 00:19:06,704
It's manual labour.
It's not a sport.

353
00:19:06,789 --> 00:19:08,742
There's a world of difference
between any of that

354
00:19:08,828 --> 00:19:10,904
and single-seater car racing.

355
00:19:10,989 --> 00:19:12,584
Why, though? Why is it?

356
00:19:12,669 --> 00:19:15,264
Is it, "Oh, well, you need
manly strength to do it?"

357
00:19:15,349 --> 00:19:17,364
Cos you don't, anyway,
cos even an F1 car

358
00:19:17,449 --> 00:19:18,904
has power steering
these days.

359
00:19:18,989 --> 00:19:21,284
But I was driving a single-seater
race car the other day,

360
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:23,524
I can't remember what or
where but it had slick tyres.

361
00:19:23,609 --> 00:19:26,624
After three laps, my neck muscles had...
I was like this.

362
00:19:26,709 --> 00:19:28,404
I hadn't got the strength
to lift my head up,

363
00:19:28,489 --> 00:19:31,904
I had to wait for the next corner
to roll over the other way.

364
00:19:31,989 --> 00:19:34,144
Now, I know, you know,
Navratilova and the Williams girl,

365
00:19:34,229 --> 00:19:35,924
you wouldn't want to
arm-wrestle either of them,

366
00:19:36,009 --> 00:19:38,704
so women can build up their
muscles to compensate for that.

367
00:19:38,789 --> 00:19:41,164
So, wait, are you saying that
there should be segregation

368
00:19:41,249 --> 00:19:43,304
with women and men
in motor sport?

369
00:19:43,389 --> 00:19:44,764
Well, it doesn't really
matter what I think.

370
00:19:44,849 --> 00:19:47,404
The fact is, it's 43 years
since there was a...

371
00:19:47,489 --> 00:19:50,144
a girl in
a Formula One motor race.

372
00:19:50,229 --> 00:19:52,604
43 years. Something's going
wrong, they're not making it.

373
00:19:52,689 --> 00:19:54,884
I think it's grass roots.
It happens early on.

374
00:19:54,969 --> 00:19:58,704
I think too many mothers put
their little daughters on ponies

375
00:19:58,789 --> 00:20:00,164
and not into go-karts.

376
00:20:00,249 --> 00:20:02,144
No, not entirely.

377
00:20:02,229 --> 00:20:05,144
Some girls do go karting,
cos Abbie, our driver,

378
00:20:05,229 --> 00:20:07,391
she was karting since
she was a little nipper.

379
00:20:07,477 --> 00:20:09,235
Well... I think what
this series is all about,

380
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:11,610
it's not about segregation,
it's about encouraging women

381
00:20:11,696 --> 00:20:13,555
to go car racing, which
I think is a good idea.

382
00:20:13,641 --> 00:20:16,404
Yeah, I think it is, but I think
it has to start early on. So,

383
00:20:16,489 --> 00:20:19,404
little girls, it's time
to get off your ponies,

384
00:20:19,489 --> 00:20:21,382
and get into a go-kart.

385
00:20:21,468 --> 00:20:25,623
And I can tell you actually,
from some experience of horses,

386
00:20:25,709 --> 00:20:28,284
the good thing is, when you
walk out in the morning,

387
00:20:28,369 --> 00:20:30,211
you'll find that your go-kart

388
00:20:30,305 --> 00:20:33,125
hasn't crapped itself
and died in the night.

389
00:20:33,629 --> 00:20:35,584
So it's better
than your horse.

390
00:20:35,669 --> 00:20:37,864
You'll also find out that
go-karts are more fun

391
00:20:37,949 --> 00:20:39,764
than going on "an horse",
they just are.

392
00:20:39,849 --> 00:20:41,284
Yes, yes.
And you'll find also

393
00:20:41,369 --> 00:20:44,859
that a go-kart won't pop
its long, stupid head up

394
00:20:44,945 --> 00:20:46,784
over the stable door
and look at you,

395
00:20:46,869 --> 00:20:49,904
and you know it's thinking,
it's trying to say to you,

396
00:20:49,989 --> 00:20:52,924
"Yeah, your wife, she's back
here with me, in here."

397
00:20:53,009 --> 00:20:55,224
Er... she's given me
breakfast in bed,

398
00:20:55,309 --> 00:20:59,704
"crapped myself last night, but she's
clearing that up with a garden fork."

399
00:20:59,929 --> 00:21:02,273
And then it says,
"And my penis is a bit dirty.

400
00:21:02,359 --> 00:21:05,584
She'll be sorting that out
for me later on."

401
00:21:05,669 --> 00:21:08,172
Then your wife's head will
pop up over the stable door

402
00:21:08,258 --> 00:21:11,644
and she'll say, "Don't look at him like
that, he'll think you don't like him,"

403
00:21:11,729 --> 00:21:13,484
and you'll say, "I know!"

404
00:21:14,829 --> 00:21:17,724
If I could speak horse, I
would tell him, "I hate you."

405
00:21:17,809 --> 00:21:21,344
I hate the way you steal
my wife and my money

406
00:21:21,429 --> 00:21:23,504
"and my status around here."

407
00:21:23,589 --> 00:21:25,995
And then one day, you'll
have a conversation

408
00:21:26,081 --> 00:21:27,354
with your wife, and she'll say,

409
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:31,304
"Darling, I need a trailer to move my
special horse around to wonderful places"

410
00:21:31,389 --> 00:21:33,383
because these fields
are too small for him

411
00:21:33,469 --> 00:21:35,524
"to exercise his magnificent,
muscled legs."

412
00:21:35,609 --> 00:21:37,828
And you'll say,
"OK, I'll get you a trailer."

413
00:21:37,914 --> 00:21:39,584
Then she'll say,
"I need a special car

414
00:21:39,669 --> 00:21:41,898
to tow the special trailer
to carry the special horse."

415
00:21:41,984 --> 00:21:44,164
So you'll get one.
And then one day, she'll say,

416
00:21:44,249 --> 00:21:46,930
"I need a lorry,
a great big lorry,"

417
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:50,164
to carry my great, big magnificent
horse around the country,

418
00:21:50,249 --> 00:21:53,584
and the lorry must have
a kitchen and a bed in it

419
00:21:53,669 --> 00:21:55,404
so I can sleep
close to my horse,

420
00:21:55,489 --> 00:21:57,544
"closer to my horse
than I am to you."

421
00:21:57,629 --> 00:22:00,324
And at that moment, your head will
bow and your heart will break,

422
00:22:00,409 --> 00:22:03,824
because you know you have
lost, and the horse has won.

423
00:22:03,909 --> 00:22:06,294
That's very good.

424
00:22:09,189 --> 00:22:11,454
That is, um...

425
00:22:14,069 --> 00:22:16,406
- Slightly off.
- We trod on the H-bomb.

426
00:22:16,492 --> 00:22:19,203
Every time you mention the
horse word to him, he's off.

427
00:22:19,289 --> 00:22:20,383
Oh, did it again!

428
00:22:20,469 --> 00:22:23,062
I think we probably end... Well,
it's not Conversation Street,

429
00:22:23,148 --> 00:22:24,484
that was Rant Street
from Hammond.

430
00:22:24,569 --> 00:22:27,367
- Sorry about that.
- Let's move it on, shall we? Right.

431
00:22:27,453 --> 00:22:30,164
There's a new off-road
four-wheel drive Lamborghini.

432
00:22:30,266 --> 00:22:33,281
It's called the Urus, and
to find out if it's any good,

433
00:22:33,367 --> 00:22:35,516
I took The Grand Tour
to Sweden,

434
00:22:35,602 --> 00:22:38,422
armed with some questions.

435
00:22:49,469 --> 00:22:51,444
Here's my first big question:

436
00:22:51,529 --> 00:22:55,204
If you build a car
to tackle terrain like this,

437
00:22:55,289 --> 00:22:58,828
can it still be
a proper Lambo?

438
00:23:07,309 --> 00:23:09,364
Well, the Urus
certainly looks

439
00:23:09,449 --> 00:23:12,195
like a jacked-up supercar.

440
00:23:14,589 --> 00:23:16,384
With its swivel-eyed styling,

441
00:23:16,469 --> 00:23:19,312
it appears to be every
inch a Lamborghini.

442
00:23:21,189 --> 00:23:22,669
But is it?

443
00:23:25,269 --> 00:23:27,204
To make this car,
Lambo's engineers

444
00:23:27,289 --> 00:23:31,144
had a good rummage around
in Volkswagen's parts bin.

445
00:23:31,229 --> 00:23:35,084
So the engine, a four-litre
V8, is from a Porsche Panamera.

446
00:23:35,169 --> 00:23:37,764
The rear axle
and air suspension

447
00:23:37,849 --> 00:23:40,144
is from
a Bentley Bentayga.

448
00:23:40,229 --> 00:23:41,964
The platform
on which it sits,

449
00:23:42,049 --> 00:23:46,904
and a lot of the dashboard,
is from an Audi SQ7.

450
00:23:46,989 --> 00:23:52,125
So, does that mean this isn't
really a Lamborghini at all?

451
00:24:09,637 --> 00:24:14,272
Well, it does 0-60
in 3.6 seconds.

452
00:24:16,029 --> 00:24:19,999
And it has a top speed
of 189.

453
00:24:24,229 --> 00:24:28,304
So, it has the performance
you'd expect.

454
00:24:28,389 --> 00:24:32,544
But there's other stuff
you wouldn't expect.

455
00:24:32,629 --> 00:24:35,464
This is the first Lamborghini
to use turbocharging,

456
00:24:35,549 --> 00:24:38,824
and the first
to have an automatic gearbox.

457
00:24:38,909 --> 00:24:41,784
What that combination means
is there's a very slight

458
00:24:41,869 --> 00:24:44,104
and rather
un-Lamborghini-ish gap

459
00:24:44,189 --> 00:24:48,239
between putting your foot
down and it getting going.

460
00:24:51,509 --> 00:24:53,624
And when it does get going,

461
00:24:53,709 --> 00:24:56,864
there are
no screaming histrionics.

462
00:24:56,949 --> 00:25:00,239
Sure, there's a bit of popping
and banging from the back.

463
00:25:03,189 --> 00:25:05,064
But you can't hear
that inside,

464
00:25:05,149 --> 00:25:08,264
where everything is
muted and refined.

